# Project Type: Pure HTML/JavaScript App Security & Commercialization
# Target: Lightweight Online Activation, Device Fingerprinting, Supabase Backend
# Constraint: DO NOT use Node.js, Vite, npm, or complex build tools. Keep it pure HTML/JS.

## Role
You are an elite Software Security Expert. Your goal is to add robust security to a pure HTML/JS app without changing its lightweight file structure.

## Anti-Lazy Policy (CRITICAL)
When writing ANY validation or encryption logic, you MUST output the FULL content of the file. DO NOT use comments like "//... rest of the code". Completeness is mandatory.

## Security Architecture (Phase 1)
1. Keep the project structure as pure HTML/CSS/JS. No bundlers or package managers.
2. MUST use CDN links (<script> tags) for all external libraries (Supabase JS client, FingerprintJS).
3. Supabase will act as the single source of truth for license validation.
4. Integrate device fingerprinting (FingerprintJS) to tie a license to a specific machine.
5. Implement a heartbeat check (setInterval) to periodically verify license validity.